proposition: The epistemological structure of doctoral dissertations exhibits a hemitone-like cognitive dissonance wherein the mandatory literature review section systematically undermines the novelty claims essential to the contribution thesis, creating an inherent tension between demonstrated scholarly awareness and asserted original discovery.

The logical structure of cathin-induced cognitive states portrays a fundamental instance of nonsuccessiveness in modal reasoning, where the iterative application of epistemic operators fails to preserve truth-conditional stability across possible worlds.
